Example:
	bsdtagconv 'gbk,ascii;big5,ascii' -i zhtw:zhtw_words --auto blah.mp3
	argv[1] is ';' joined from-conversion, for decoding tags which use
	legacy charset/encoding (eg. id3v1).
	bsdtagconv will choose the best result.

Dependencies:
	bsdconv-5.0
	audio/taglib

todo:
	ID3v2: force v2.3 and utf-16le

Bugs:
	strip() does not strip cleanly
